				 Cartel cloud on pig iron
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Oct. 5: The Engineering Export Promotion Council will submit a memorandum to Bengal chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on the alleged emergence of a cartel in the pig iron industry.																								Pig iron is the key input in castings which constitute the bulk of engineering exports from the eastern region.																								Council chairman Rakesh Shah said, We will urge the chief minister to have a word with the Union steel ministry on the issue of pig iron prices and cartel formation. 																								Pig iron prices have jumped by Rs 2,000 per tonne this month. On Thursday, the prices went up by Rs 400.																								VAT refund																								R.S. Gujral, director-general of foreign trade, today said his department would take up with the state the issue of VAT refund of Rs 34 crore to exporters.
